# ‚ö° GPU Setup Guide for Intra Algo (Windows)

This guide explains how to enable **TensorFlow GPU acceleration** on **Windows** for use with the Intra Algo platform.

---

## ‚úÖ Why Use GPU?

GPU acceleration significantly improves the speed of training deep learning models like CNNs.
TensorFlow will automatically use the GPU if properly installed and configured.

---

## ‚ö†Ô∏è Compatibility Checklist

| Requirement            | Status |
|------------------------|--------|
| ‚úÖ NVIDIA GPU (RTX etc) | Yes    |
| ‚úÖ Python 3.10           | Required |
| ‚úÖ TensorFlow 2.10.0     | Required |
| ‚úÖ DirectML Plugin       | Optional (used here) |
| ‚úÖ NVIDIA GPU Driver     | Up to date (check `nvidia-smi`) |

---

## üõ†Ô∏è Setup Steps

### 1. ‚úÖ Install Python 3.10

Download and install from:
https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-3100/

Make sure to **add Python to PATH** during setup.

---

### 2. ‚úÖ Create New Virtual Environment

```bash
python3.10 -m venv dml_venv
